澳大利亚的LGBT人群免受歧视并享有与其他人相同的权利和责任。1975年至1997年间，各州和地区逐步废除可追溯到[[大英帝国|大英帝国]]时代的反同性恋法律。<ref name=carbery>{{cite journal |last=Carbery |first=Graham |title=Towards Homosexual Equality in Australian Criminal Law: A Brief History |year=2010 |edition=2nd |issue= |pages= |url=http://www.alga.org.au/files/towardsequality2ed.pdf |publisher=Australian Lesbian and Gay Archives Inc. |journal= |access-date=2019-05-19 |archive-date=2019-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190305143829/https://www.alga.org.au/files/towardsequality2ed.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>澳大利亞於2017年12月9日將同性婚姻合法化。自2003年起，各州和地区开始向同性伴侣发放家庭伴侣关系福利和关系承认，联邦法律自2009年起承认同性伴侣为事实上的伴侣关系。除了婚姻之外，同性关系可以通过各种方式得到州或地区的承认，包括通过[[民事结合|民事结合]]，家庭伴侣关系，注册关系和/或未注册的[[事实上|事实]]关系。<ref name="sheldrick-oseas">{{cite news|last1=Sheldrick|first1=Drew|title=Overseas same-sex marriage recognition back in the spotlight|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/topics/sexuality/article/2016/02/04/overseas-same-sex-marriage-recognition-back-spotlight?cid=inbody:knowing-your-adoption-and-foster-care-rights-as-an-lgbtqia-person|accessdate=2016-12-04|agency=Special Broadcasting Service|date=2016-02-04|archive-date=2019-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404171646/https://www.sbs.com.au/topics/sexuality/article/2016/02/04/overseas-same-sex-marriage-recognition-back-spotlight?cid=inbody:knowing-your-adoption-and-foster-care-rights-as-an-lgbtqia-person|dead-url=no}}</ref>

澳大利亚的跨性别权利包括修改一个人在出生证等官方记录上的性别合法性，尽管有些司法管辖区要求首先进行[[性别重置手术|性别重置手术]]。<ref name="cert-reform-call">{{cite news|last1=Wiggins|first1=Nick|title=Transgender, intersex people call for birth certificate reforms|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-08-25/transgender-lbgti-birth-certificate-discrimination/7786286|accessdate=2016-09-17|work=ABC News|agency=Australian Broadcasting Corporation|date=2016-08-25|language=en-AU|archive-date=2019-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190409003525/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-08-25/transgender-lbgti-birth-certificate-discrimination/7786286|dead-url=no}}</ref>然而，澳大利亚的双性人权利得不到充分保护，许多双性澳大利亚人在童年时期面临强制性医疗干预。<ref>{{cite web |last1=Koch |first1=Cornelia |last2=Wisdom |first2=Travis |title=Surgery to make intersex children 'normal' should be banned |url=https://theconversation.com/surgery-to-make-intersex-children-normal-should-be-banned-76952 |website=The Conversation |accessdate=2019-02-08 |language=en |date=2017-07-05 |archive-date=2019-04-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190426201412/http://theconversation.com/surgery-to-make-intersex-children-normal-should-be-banned-76952 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

澳大利亚被公认为世界上对同性恋最友好的国家之一<ref>{{cite news|title=The 20 most and least gay-friendly countries in the world|url=https://www.pri.org/stories/2013-06-26/20-most-and-least-gay-friendly-countries-world|accessdate=2017-12-31|date=2013-06-26|work=Public Radio International|archive-date=2017-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171011035554/https://www.pri.org/stories/2013-06-26/20-most-and-least-gay-friendly-countries-world|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Calcutt|first1=Mike|title=Be Free And Be Gay! The Top 10 Gay Friendly Countries In The World|url=https://www.therichest.com/expensive-lifestyle/lifestyle/e-free-and-be-gay-the-top-10-gay-friendly-countries-in-the-world/|accessdate=2017-12-31|work=TheRichest|publisher=Valnet Inc|date=2014-09-01|archive-date=2019-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404142812/https://www.therichest.com/expensive-lifestyle/lifestyle/e-free-and-be-gay-the-top-10-gay-friendly-countries-in-the-world/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Glover|first1=Richard|title=Australia’s strange vote on same-sex marriage|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/global-opinions/wp/2017/09/04/australias-strange-vote-on-same-sex-marriage/|accessdate=2017-12-31|work=Washington Post|date=2017-09-04|archive-date=2019-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404144455/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/global-opinions/wp/2017/09/04/australias-strange-vote-on-same-sex-marriage/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。民意调查和澳大利亚婚姻法邮政调查表明，人们普遍支持[[同性婚姻|同性婚姻]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aph.gov.au/Parliamentary_Business/Committees/House_of_Representatives_Committees?url=spla/bill%20marriage/report.htm|title=House of Representatives Committees|publisher=|accessdate=2015-07-26|archive-date=2021-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210320123107/https://www.aph.gov.au/Parliamentary_Business/Committees/House_of_Representatives_Committees?url=spla%2Fbill%20marriage%2Freport.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Karp|first1=Paul|title=Marriage equality law passes Australia's parliament in landslide vote|url=https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2017/dec/07/marriage-equality-law-passes-australias-parliament-in-landslide-vote|accessdate=2017-12-10|work=The Guardian|date=2017-12-07|archive-date=2019-05-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190520055412/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2017/dec/07/marriage-equality-law-passes-australias-parliament-in-landslide-vote|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2013年[[皮尤研究中心|皮尤研究中心]]调查发现，79％的澳大利亚人认为同性恋应该被社会接受，使其成为调查的第五大支持国<ref name="pewpoll">{{cite web |url=http://www.pewglobal.org/2013/06/04/the-global-divide-on-homosexuality/ |title=The Global Divide on Homosexuality |date=2013-06-04 |publisher=[[皮尤研究中心|皮尤研究中心]] |accessdate=2014-05-16 |archive-date=2013-11-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103034522/http://www.pewglobal.org/2013/06/04/the-global-divide-on-homosexuality/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=globalpost>{{cite web|url=http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/politics/130607/the-20-most-and-least-gay-friendly-countries-the-world|title=The 20 most and least gay-friendly countries in the world|work=Global Post|accessdate=2014-05-16|date=2013-06-26|archive-date=2016-07-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160727172945/http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/politics/130607/the-20-most-and-least-gay-friendly-countries-the-world|dead-url=no}}</ref>。凭借其长期的LGBT活动历史和年度男女同性恋狂欢节，[[悉尼|悉尼]]被评为澳大利亚和全世界对同性恋最友好的城市之一。<ref name="The Independent">{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/love-sex/taboo-tolerance/the-ten-best-places-in-the-world-to-be-gay-932557.html?action=gallery&ino=2|title=Sydney Things have changed enormously since the first Mardi Gras march was|work=The Independent|accessdate=2015-07-26|archive-date=2019-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404142953/https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/love-sex/taboo-tolerance/the-ten-best-places-in-the-world-to-be-gay-932557.html?action=gallery&ino=2|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 歷史 ==
1990年代以來一直成為[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]]具爭議性的社會議題。

2004年，澳大利亞重修《婚姻法》時，將婚姻只限異性兩者合法結合。<ref>[http://www.comlaw.gov.au/comlaw/Legislation/Act1.nsf/0/91DFFD1199DF26D8CA2574170007CE06/$file/1262004.pdf Marriage Amendment Act 2004] {{Wayback|url=http://www.comlaw.gov.au/comlaw/Legislation/Act1.nsf/0/91DFFD1199DF26D8CA2574170007CE06/$file/1262004.pdf |date=20150706163426 }}, ComLaw</ref> 雖然如此，自2009年7月1日，男女同性戀伴侶將與異性戀配偶享有相同的權利，如養老金、賦稅、社會安全、勞工補償、醫藥津貼等，只是仍然不能結婚。

特恩布尔政府立法向议会提出将于2017年2月举行同性婚姻公民投票，尽管这被澳大利亚参议院否决。反对派工党在其党纲中支持同性婚姻，但允许其议会成员对同性婚姻立法进行良心投票。

澳大利亚婚姻法邮政调查显示61.6％支持同性婚姻。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/datablog/ng-interactive/2017/nov/15/same-sex-marriage-survey-how-australia-voted-electorate-by-electorate|title=Full results of Australia's vote for same-sex marriage, electorate by electorate – interactive|last=Evershed|first=Nick|work=The Guardian|access-date=2017-11-15|last2=Evershed|first2=Nick|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=2019-04-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420105228/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/datablog/ng-interactive/2017/nov/15/same-sex-marriage-survey-how-australia-voted-electorate-by-electorate|dead-url=no}}</ref>在结果公布后不久，议会将一项将同性婚姻合法化的法案提交议会，2017年11月29日参议院以43票对12票通过，并于2017年12月7日在众议院通过。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-11-29/same-sex-marriage-bill-passes-senate/9202478|title=Same-sex marriage bill passes Senate with day to spare before House of Representatives resumes|work=ABC News|date=2017-11-29|accessdate=2019-05-19|archive-date=2018-09-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180906125519/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-11-29/same-sex-marriage-bill-passes-senate/9202478|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-12-07/same-sex-marriage-bill-passes-house-of-representatives/9235560|title=Same-sex marriage bill passes House of Representatives, paving way for first gay weddings|work=ABC News|date=2017-12-07|accessdate=2019-05-19|archive-date=2019-03-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190324194919/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-12-07/same-sex-marriage-bill-passes-house-of-representatives/9235560|dead-url=no}}</ref>该法案于2017年12月8日获得御准，并于次日生效。<ref name="RoyalAssent2017">{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-12-08/same-sex-marriage-legal-after-gg-approval/9239334|title=Same-sex marriage signed into law by Governor-General, first weddings to happen from January 9|work=ABC News|date=2017-12-08|accessdate=2019-05-19|archive-date=2017-12-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171207223146/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2017-12-08/same-sex-marriage-legal-after-gg-approval/9239334|dead-url=no}}</ref>2017年12月15日根据澳大利亚法律产生第一例合法同性婚姻。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-03-07/heartbreaking-story-behind-australias-first-same-sex-marriage/9523098|title=Heartbreaking story behind Australia's first same-sex marriage revealed|work=ABC News|date=2018-03-07|accessdate=2018-03-07|author=Patrick Williams|archive-date=2018-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181001042513/http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-03-07/heartbreaking-story-behind-australias-first-same-sex-marriage/9523098|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theage.com.au/national/australias-first-samesex-couples-says-i-do-20171216-h05v7s.html|title=Australia's first same-sex couples say 'I do'|date=2017-12-16|access-date=2017-12-16|publisher=[[Fairfax_Media|Fairfax Media]]|work=[[The_Age|The Age]]|author=Julie Power & Goya Dmytryshchak|archive-date=2017-12-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171217023011/http://www.theage.com.au/national/australias-first-samesex-couples-says-i-do-20171216-h05v7s.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 政党現況 ==
澳大利亚政党在LGBT权利问题上两极分化，得到[[澳洲綠黨|澳洲綠黨]]和[[澳大利亞工黨|澳大利亞工黨]]等中左翼政党以及中右翼[[澳大利亚自由党|澳大利亚自由党]]的温和派成员的支持。<ref name="fear">{{cite news|last1=Altman|first1=Dennis|title=Fear and loathing reigns in Safe Schools and same-sex marriage debates|url=https://theconversation.com/fear-and-loathing-reigns-in-safe-schools-and-same-sex-marriage-debates-56347|accessdate=2016-12-16|work=The Conversation|date=2016-03-21|archive-date=2019-04-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420124842/http://theconversation.com/fear-and-loathing-reigns-in-safe-schools-and-same-sex-marriage-debates-56347|dead-url=no}}</ref>在州和地区一级，大多数LGBTI法律改革都是由澳大利亚工党政府承担的。<ref name="millbank-couples">{{cite journal|last1=Millbank|first1=Jenni|title=Recognition of Lesbian and Gay Families in Australian Law - Part One: Couples|journal=Federal Law Review|date=2006|volume=34|issue=1|page=1|url=http://www.austlii.edu.au/au/journals/FedLRev/2006/1.html|accessdate=2017-09-12|archive-date=2020-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203232504/http://www.austlii.edu.au/au/journals/FedLRev/2006/1.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>而保守派則大部分傾向反對，但普遍認為可以立法保障LGBT人士不受歧視。

